(162, 12, 'JavaScript Array Methods', 'Métodos de matriz de JavaScript', 'JavaScript Array Methods List with English Descriptions\r\n\r\nBasic array methods\r\n\r\npush adds an element to the end of the array\r\npop removes the last element from the array\r\nunshift adds an element to the beginning of the array\r\nshift removes the first element from the array\r\nconcat combines two or more arrays into one\r\njoin joins all elements of the array into a string\r\nslice returns a portion of the array without modifying it\r\nsplice adds removes or replaces elements in the array modifying the original\r\nindexOf returns the index of the first matching element\r\nlastIndexOf returns the index of the last matching element\r\nincludes checks if an array contains a specific element\r\nreverse reverses the order of the elements in the array\r\nsort sorts the elements in the array alphabetically or numerically\r\n\r\nIteration and transformation methods\r\n\r\nforEach executes a function once for each array element\r\nmap creates a new array by applying a function to each element\r\nfilter creates a new array with elements that pass a test\r\nfind returns the first element that satisfies a test function\r\nfindIndex returns the index of the first element that satisfies a test\r\nevery returns true if all elements pass a test\r\nsome returns true if at least one element passes a test\r\nreduce applies a function to reduce the array to a single value\r\nflat flattens nested arrays into a single level array\r\nflatMap maps and then flattens the result into a new array\r\n\r\nAdditional useful methods\r\n\r\nfill fills all or part of the array with a static value\r\ncopyWithin copies part of the array to another location in the same array\r\nat returns the element at a specific index supports negative indexing\r\ntoString converts the array to a string\r\nArray isArray checks whether a variable is an array\r\n\r\nJavaScript Functions\r\n\r\nFunctions are reusable blocks of code that perform a task\r\n\r\nFunction declaration example\r\n\r\nfunction greet name returns Hello followed by the name\r\n\r\nArrow functions\r\n\r\nArrow functions are a shorter syntax for writing functions\r\n\r\nExample of arrow function that adds two numbers\r\n\r\nconst add equals open parenthesis a comma b close parenthesis arrow a plus b\r\n\r\nIf the function has only one parameter you can omit the parentheses\r\n\r\nExample\r\n\r\nconst square equals x arrow x times x\r\n\r\nArrow functions are useful for callbacks and concise code\r\n\r\nJavaScript Variables\r\n\r\nVariables store data values\r\n\r\nYou can declare variables using var let or const\r\n\r\nLet is block scoped and preferred over var\r\n\r\nConst is used for constants that do not change\r\n\r\nExample\r\n\r\nlet count equals 0\r\n\r\nconst pi equals 3 point 1416\r\n\r\nYou can update let variables but not const variables\r\n\r\nJavaScript Conditionals\r\n\r\nConditional statements allow decision making in code\r\n\r\nIf statement runs code if a condition is true\r\n\r\nElse runs code if the condition is false\r\n\r\nExample\r\n\r\nif count greater than 10 open brace\r\n\r\nconsole dot log Count is greater than ten\r\n\r\nclose brace else open brace\r\n\r\nconsole dot log Count is ten or less\r\n\r\nclose brace\r\n\r\nJavaScript Loops\r\n\r\nLoops repeat code multiple times\r\n\r\nFor loop runs code a fixed number of times\r\n\r\nExample\r\n\r\nfor let i equals zero semicolon i less than five semicolon i plus plus open brace\r\n\r\nconsole dot log i\r\n\r\nclose brace\r\n\r\nWhile loop runs code while a condition is true\r\n\r\nExample\r\n\r\nwhile count less than five open brace\r\n\r\nconsole dot log count\r\n\r\ncount plus plus\r\n\r\nclose brace', '[{\"content\":\"JavaScript Array Methods List with English Descriptions\",\"translation\":\"Lista de m\\u00e9todos de matrices de JavaScript con descripciones en ingl\\u00e9s\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:32:05\"},{\"content\":\"Basic array methods\",\"translation\":\"M\\u00e9todos b\\u00e1sicos de array\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:32:16\"},{\"content\":\"push adds an element to the end of the array\",\"translation\":\"push a\\u00f1ade un elemento al final de la matriz\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:32:22\"},{\"content\":\"pop removes the last element from the array\",\"translation\":\"pop elimina el \\u00faltimo elemento de la matriz\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:32:30\"},{\"content\":\"unshift adds an element to the beginning of the array\",\"translation\":\"unshift a\\u00f1ade un elemento al principio de la matriz\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:32:38\"},{\"content\":\"shift removes the first element from the array\",\"translation\":\"shift elimina el primer elemento de la matriz\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:32:52\"},{\"content\":\"concat combines two or more arrays into one\",\"translation\":\"concat combina dos o m\\u00e1s matrices en una sola\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:33:00\"},{\"content\":\"join joins all elements of the array into a string\",\"translation\":\"join une todos los elementos de la matriz en una cadena\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:33:10\"},{\"content\":\"slice returns a portion of the array without modifying it\",\"translation\":\"slice devuelve una parte de la matriz sin modificarla\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:33:25\"},{\"content\":\"splice adds removes or replaces elements in the array modifying the original\",\"translation\":\"splice a\\u00f1ade, elimina o sustituye elementos en el array modificando el original\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:33:36\"},{\"content\":\"indexOf returns the index of the first matching element\",\"translation\":\"indexOf devuelve el \\u00edndice del primer elemento coincidente\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:33:44\"},{\"content\":\"lastIndexOf returns the index of the last matching element\",\"translation\":\"lastIndexOf devuelve el \\u00edndice del \\u00faltimo elemento coincidente\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:33:59\"},{\"content\":\"includes checks if an array contains a specific element\",\"translation\":\"incluye la comprobaci\\u00f3n de si una matriz contiene un elemento espec\\u00edfico\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:34:16\"},{\"content\":\"reverse reverses the order of the elements in the array\",\"translation\":\"reverse invierte el orden de los elementos de la matriz\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:34:16\"},{\"content\":\"sort sorts the elements in the array alphabetically or numerically\",\"translation\":\"sort ordena los elementos de la matriz alfab\\u00e9tica o num\\u00e9ricamente\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:34:19\"},{\"content\":\"Iteration and transformation methods\",\"translation\":\"M\\u00e9todos de iteraci\\u00f3n y transformaci\\u00f3n\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:34:31\"},{\"content\":\"forEach executes a function once for each array element\",\"translation\":\"forEach ejecuta una funci\\u00f3n una vez por cada elemento de la matriz\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:34:42\"},{\"content\":\"map creates a new array by applying a function to each element\",\"translation\":\"map crea una nueva matriz aplicando una funci\\u00f3n a cada elemento\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:34:58\"},{\"content\":\"filter creates a new array with elements that pass a test\",\"translation\":\"crea una nueva matriz con los elementos que superan una prueba\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:35:08\"},{\"content\":\"find returns the first element that satisfies a test function\",\"translation\":\"find devuelve el primer elemento que satisface una funci\\u00f3n de prueba\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:35:18\"},{\"content\":\"findIndex returns the index of the first element that satisfies a test\",\"translation\":\"findIndex devuelve el \\u00edndice del primer elemento que satisface una prueba\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:35:35\"},{\"content\":\"every returns true if all elements pass a test\",\"translation\":\"every devuelve verdadero si todos los elementos superan una prueba\",\"timestamp\":