(164, 12, 'Understanding Grammar Differences', 'Comprender las diferencias de gramática', 'Understanding Grammar Differences\r\n\r\nEnglish grammar often places adjectives before nouns, while Spanish usually puts them after the nouns.\r\nIn Spanish, verbs change endings to indicate subject and tense, unlike English, which often uses auxiliary verbs.\r\nEnglish pronouns rarely change form except for subject and object cases, but Spanish pronouns vary much more.\r\nArticles in English stay the same regardless of gender, while Spanish articles change for masculine and feminine.\r\nIn English, the word order is important for meaning, but Spanish allows more flexibility in sentence structure.\r\nQuestions in English require auxiliary verbs, whereas Spanish can simply change intonation to form questions.\r\nEnglish uses “do” in questions and negatives, but Spanish expresses these without an extra auxiliary verb.\r\nIn Spanish, subject pronouns are often omitted because the verb form already shows who is acting.\r\nEnglish must always include the subject, except in imperatives, to make sentences grammatically correct.\r\nSpanish adjectives agree in gender and number with nouns, while English adjectives remain unchanged.\r\nIn English, prepositions are fixed in expressions, but Spanish sometimes changes prepositions depending on context.\r\nVerb tenses in English use auxiliary verbs like “have” or “will,” while Spanish modifies the verb endings directly.\r\nEnglish modal verbs never change form, but Spanish equivalent verbs conjugate according to subject and tense.\r\nPassive voice is more common in English, while Spanish prefers active voice or reflexive constructions.\r\nEnglish relies on word order for emphasis, whereas Spanish can use different structures to highlight information.\r\nBoth languages have unique ways of expressing ideas, and understanding these differences improves communication greatly.', '[{\"content\":\"Understanding Grammar Differences\",\"translation\":\"Comprender las diferencias de gram\\u00e1tica\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 15:59:00\"},{\"content\":\"Understanding Grammar Differences\",\"translation\":\"Comprender las diferencias de gram\\u00e1tica\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 15:59:03\"},{\"content\":\"English grammar often places adjectives before nouns, while Spanish usually puts them after the nouns.\",\"translation\":\"La gram\\u00e1tica inglesa a menudo coloca adjetivos antes de los sustantivos, mientras que el espa\\u00f1ol generalmente los pone despu\\u00e9s de los sustantivos.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 15:59:05\"},{\"content\":\"In Spanish, verbs change endings to indicate subject and tense, unlike English, which often uses auxiliary verbs.\",\"translation\":\"En espa\\u00f1ol, los verbos cambian las terminaciones para indicar sujeto y tiempo, a diferencia del ingl\\u00e9s, que a menudo usa verbos auxiliares.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 15:59:14\"},{\"content\":\"English pronouns rarely change form except for subject and object cases, but Spanish pronouns vary much more.\",\"translation\":\"Los pronombres ingleses rara vez cambian la forma, excepto los casos de sujetos y objetos, pero los pronombres espa\\u00f1oles var\\u00edan mucho m\\u00e1s.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 15:59:25\"},{\"content\":\"Articles in English stay the same regardless of gender, while Spanish articles change for masculine and feminine.\",\"translation\":\"Los art\\u00edculos en ingl\\u00e9s permanecen igual independientemente del g\\u00e9nero, mientras que los art\\u00edculos espa\\u00f1oles cambian para masculinos y femeninos.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 15:59:36\"},{\"content\":\"In English, the word order is important for meaning, but Spanish allows more flexibility in sentence structure.\",\"translation\":\"En ingl\\u00e9s, el orden de la palabra es importante para el significado, pero el espa\\u00f1ol permite m\\u00e1s flexibilidad en la estructura de las oraciones.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 15:59:46\"},{\"content\":\"Questions in English require auxiliary verbs, whereas Spanish can simply change intonation to form questions.\",\"translation\":\"Las preguntas en ingl\\u00e9s requieren verbos auxiliares, mientras que el espa\\u00f1ol simplemente puede cambiar la entonaci\\u00f3n para formar preguntas.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 15:59:55\"},{\"content\":\"English uses \\u201cdo\\u201d in questions and negatives, but Spanish expresses these without an extra auxiliary verb.\",\"translation\":\"El ingl\\u00e9s usa \\\"hacer\\\" en preguntas y negativos, pero el espa\\u00f1ol los expresa sin un verbo auxiliar adicional.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 16:00:06\"},{\"content\":\"In Spanish, subject pronouns are often omitted because the verb form already shows who is acting.\",\"translation\":\"En espa\\u00f1ol, los pronombres de temas a menudo se omiten porque la forma verbal ya muestra qui\\u00e9n est\\u00e1 actuando.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 16:00:18\"},{\"content\":\"In Spanish, subject pronouns are often omitted because the verb form already shows who is acting.\",\"translation\":\"En espa\\u00f1ol, los pronombres de temas a menudo se omiten porque la forma verbal ya muestra qui\\u00e9n est\\u00e1 actuando.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 16:00:20\"},{\"content\":\"English must always include the subject, except in imperatives, to make sentences grammatically correct.\",\"translation\":\"El ingl\\u00e9s siempre debe incluir el sujeto, excepto en los imperativos, para hacer que las oraciones sean gramaticalmente correctas.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 16:00:27\"},{\"content\":\"Spanish adjectives agree in gender and number with nouns, while English adjectives remain unchanged.\",\"translation\":\"Los adjetivos espa\\u00f1oles est\\u00e1n de acuerdo en g\\u00e9nero y n\\u00famero con sustantivos, mientras que los adjetivos en ingl\\u00e9s permanecen sin cambios.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 16:00:36\"},{\"content\":\"In English, prepositions are fixed in expressions, but Spanish sometimes changes prepositions depending on context.\",\"translation\":\"En ingl\\u00e9s, las preposiciones se fijan en expresiones, pero el espa\\u00f1ol a veces cambia las preposiciones dependiendo del contexto.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 16:00:45\"},{\"content\":\"Verb tenses in English use auxiliary verbs like \\u201chave\\u201d or \\u201cwill,\\u201d while Spanish modifies the verb endings directly.\",\"translation\":\"Los tiempos verbales en ingl\\u00e9s usan verbos auxiliares como \\\"tener\\\" o \\\"voluntad\\\", mientras que el espa\\u00f1ol modifica las terminaciones verbales directamente.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 16:00:56\"},{\"content\":\"Understanding Grammar Differences\",\"translation\":\"Comprender las diferencias de gram\\u00e1tica\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 16:14:48\"},{\"content\":\"Understanding Grammar Differences\",\"translation\":\"Comprender las diferencias de gram\\u00e1tica\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 16:14:50\"},{\"content\":\"Understanding Grammar Differences\",\"translation\":\"Comprender las diferencias gramaticales\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-03 05:33:38\"},{\"content\":\"Understanding Grammar Differences\",\"translation\":\"Comprender las diferencias gramaticales\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-03 05:37:04\"},{\"content\":\"Understanding Grammar Differences\",\"translation\":\"Comprender las diferencias gramaticales\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-03 05:37:42\"},{\"content\":\"Understanding Grammar Differences\",\"translation\":\"Comprender las diferencias gramaticales\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-03 05:53:37\"},{\"content\":\"Understanding Grammar Differences\",\"translation\":\"Comprender las diferencias gramaticales\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-03 06:44:11\"},{\"content\":\"Understanding Grammar Differences\",\"translation\":\"Comprender las diferencias gramaticales\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-03 06:45:56\"},{\"content\":\"Understanding Grammar Differences\",\"translation\":\"Comprender las diferencias gramaticales\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-03 10:32:42\"},{\"content\":\"Understanding Grammar Differences\",\"translation\":\"Comprender las diferencias gramaticales\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-04 12:30:44\"},{\"content\":\"Understanding Grammar Differences\",\"translation\":\"Comprender las diferencias gramaticales\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-04 12:31:01\"},{\"content\":\"Understanding Grammar Differences\",\"translation\":\"Comprender las diferencias gramaticales\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-04 12:31:29\"},{\"content\":\"English modal verbs never change form, but Spanish equivalent verbs conjugate according to subject and tense.\",\"translation\":\"Los verbos modales ingleses nunca cambian de forma, pero los verbos equivalentes espa\\u00f1oles se conjugan seg\\u00fan el sujeto y el tiempo.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-04 12:35:48\"},{\"content\":\"Passive voice is more common in English, while Spanish prefers active voice or reflexive constructions.\",\"translation\":\"La voz pasiva es m\\u00e1s com\\u00fan en ingl\\u00e9s, mientras que el espa\\u00f1ol prefiere la voz activa o las construcciones reflexivas.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-04 12:36:06\"},{\"content\":\"English relies on word order for emphasis, whereas Spanish can use different structures to highlight information.\",\"translation\":\"El ingl\\u00e9s se basa en el orden de las palabras para dar \\u00e9nfasis, mientras que el espa\\u00f1ol puede utilizar diferentes estructuras para resaltar la informaci\\u00f3n.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-04 12:36:30\"},{\"content\":\"Both languages have unique ways of expressing ideas, and understanding these differences improves communication greatly.\",\"translation\":\"Ambas lenguas tienen formas \\u00fanicas de expresar las ideas, y comprender estas diferencias mejora enormemente la comunicaci\\u00f3n.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-04 12:36:48\"},{\"content\":\"Understanding Grammar Differences\",\"translation\":\"Comprender las diferencias gramaticales\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-04 12:42:16\"},{\"content\":\"Understanding Grammar Differences\",\"translation\":\"Comprender las diferencias gramaticales\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-04 13:17:10\"},{\"content\":\"Understanding Grammar Differences\",\"translation\":\"Comprender las diferencias gramaticales\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-04 14:03:55\"},{\"content\":\"Understanding Grammar Differences\",\"translation\":\"Comprender las diferencias gramaticales\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-20 13:32:39\"},{\"content\":\"Understanding Grammar Differences\",\"translation\":\"Comprender las diferencias gramaticales\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-21 14:04:08\"},{\"content\":\"Understanding Grammar Differences\",\"translation\":\"Comprender las diferencias gramaticales\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-11-09 14:40:29\"},{\"content\":\"Understanding Grammar Differences\",\"translation\":\"Comprender las diferencias gramaticales\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-11-09 14:42:30\"},{\"content\":\"Understanding Grammar Differences\",\"translation\":\"Comprender las diferencias gramaticales\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-12-23 21:32:07\"},{\"content\":\"English grammar often places adjectives before nouns, while Spanish usually puts them after the nouns.\",\"translation\":\"La gram\\u00e1tica inglesa suele anteponer los adjetivos a los sustantivos, mientras que la espa\\u00f1ola suele colocarlos despu\\u00e9s de \\u00e9stos.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-12-23 21:32:10\"}]', 1, 35, '2025-08-10 11:58:04'),
(166, 22, 'The Forgotten Library', 'La biblioteca olvidada', 'La biblioteca olvidada\r\nIn a quiet town, there stood an abandoned library.\r\nDust covered every book, and silence ruled the halls.\r\nPeople passed by daily, never daring to step inside.\r\n\r\nOne day, Clara, a curious student, noticed the locked door.\r\nHer love for literature made the place irresistible to explore.\r\nShe carried a lantern, trembling, yet eager to discover secrets.\r\n\r\nInside, the shelves leaned, tired from holding forgotten worlds.\r\nPages whispered faintly, as if longing for human company again.\r\nClara touched a novel, and suddenly the air shifted.\r\n\r\nThe library awakened, glowing softly under her cautious steps.\r\nCharacters walked from books, murmuring fragments of lost stories.\r\nShakespearean heroes greeted her, Dickensâ€™ ghosts sang of forgotten streets.\r\n\r\nClara realized she wasnâ€™t just reading, she was inside.\r\nThe library became alive because someone cared to listen.\r\nEvery story she touched rebuilt the crumbling walls of memory.\r\n\r\nNight after night, she returned, restoring the libraryâ€™s fading strength.\r\nHer classmates laughed, believing she wasted time on old books.\r\nBut Clara knew she wasnâ€™t saving books; they saved her.\r\n\r\nThrough stories, she found courage, wisdom, and a thousand voices.\r\nThe library, once forgotten, became her most loyal companion.\r\nLiterature proved itself timeless, breathing through whoever dares to read.', '[{\"content\":\"In a quiet town, there stood an abandoned library.\",\"translation\":\"En un pueblo tranquilo, hab\\u00eda una biblioteca abandonada.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-20 13:30:22\"},{\"content\":\"Dust covered every book, and silence ruled the halls.\",\"translation\":\"El polvo cubr\\u00eda todos los libros y el silencio reinaba en los pasillos.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-20 13:30:27\"},{\"content\":\"In a quiet town, there stood an abandoned library.\",\"translation\":\"En un pueblo tranquilo, hab\\u00eda una biblioteca abandonada.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-20 13:34:54\"},{\"content\":\"People passed by daily, never daring to step inside.\",\"translation\":\"La gente pasaba a diario, sin atreverse nunca a entrar.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-20 13:35:06\"},{\"content\":\"One day, Clara, a curious student, noticed the locked door.\",\"translation\":\"Un d\\u00eda, Clara, una alumna curiosa, se fij\\u00f3 en la puerta cerrada.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-20 13:35:10\"},{\"content\":\"Her love for literature made the place irresistible to explore.\",\"translation\":\"Su amor por la literatura hizo irresistible explorar el lugar.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-20 13:35:16\"},{\"content\":\"She carried a lantern, trembling, yet eager to discover secrets.\",\"translation\":\"Llevaba una linterna, temblorosa, pero ansiosa por descubrir secretos.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-20 13:35:20\"},{\"content\":\"Inside, the shelves leaned, tired from holding forgotten worlds.\",\"translation\":\"Dentro, las estanter\\u00edas se inclinaban, cansadas de contener mundos olvidados.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-20 13:35:37\"},{\"content\":\"Pages whispered faintly, as if longing for human company again.\",\"translation\":\"Susurraron d\\u00e9bilmente las p\\u00e1ginas, como si anhelaran de nuevo la compa\\u00f1\\u00eda humana.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-20 13:35:42\"},{\"content\":\"Clara touched a novel, and suddenly the air shifted.\",\"translation\":\"Clara toc\\u00f3 una novela y, de repente, el aire cambi\\u00f3.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-20 13:35:47\"},{\"content\":\"The library awakened, glowing softly under her cautious steps.\",\"translation\":\"La biblioteca se despert\\u00f3, brillando suavemente bajo sus pasos cautelosos.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-20 13:35:51\"},{\"content\":\"Characters walked from books, murmuring fragments of lost stories.\",\"translation\":\"Los personajes sal\\u00edan de los libros, murmurando fragmentos de historias perdidas.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-20 13:35:56\"},{\"content\":\"Shakespearean heroes greeted her, Dickens\\u2019 ghosts sang of forgotten streets.\",\"translation\":\"Los h\\u00e9roes de Shakespeare la saludaban, los fantasmas de Dickens cantaban a las calles olvidadas.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-20 13:36:00\"},{\"content\":\"Clara realized she wasn\\u2019t just reading, she was inside.\",\"translation\":\"Clara se dio cuenta de que no s\\u00f3lo estaba leyendo, sino que estaba dentro.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-20 13:36:06\"},{\"content\":\"Clara realized she wasn\\u2019t just reading, she was inside.\",\"translation\":\"Clara se dio cuenta de que no s\\u00f3lo estaba leyendo, sino que estaba dentro.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-20 13:36:06\"},{\"content\":\"The library became alive because someone cared to listen.\",\"translation\":\"La biblioteca cobr\\u00f3 vida porque alguien se preocup\\u00f3 de escuchar.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-20 13:36:10\"},{\"content\":\"Every story she touched rebuilt the crumbling walls of memory.\",\"translation\":\"Cada historia que tocaba reconstru\\u00eda los muros derruidos de la memoria.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-20 13:36:24\"},{\"content\":\"Night after night, she returned, restoring the library\\u2019s fading strength.\",\"translation\":\"Noche tras noche, volv\\u00eda a restaurar la fuerza de la biblioteca.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-20 13:36:36\"},{\"content\":\"Her classmates laughed, believing she wasted time on old books.\",\"translation\":\"Sus compa\\u00f1eros se re\\u00edan, creyendo que perd\\u00eda el tiempo con libros viejos.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-20 13:36:41\"},{\"content\":\"But Clara knew she wasn\\u2019t saving books; they saved her.\",\"translation\":\"Pero Clara sab\\u00eda que no salvaba libros, sino que ellos la salvaban a ella.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-20 13:36:52\"},{\"content\":\"Through stories, she found courage, wisdom, and a thousand voices.\",\"translation\":\"A trav\\u00e9s de las historias, encontr\\u00f3 valor, sabidur\\u00eda y mil voces.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-20 13:36:57\"},{\"content\":\"The library, once forgotten, became her most loyal companion.\",\"translation\":\"La biblioteca, antes olvidada, se convirti\\u00f3 en su m\\u00e1s fiel compa\\u00f1era.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-20 13:37:02\"},{\"content\":\"Literature proved itself timeless, breathing through whoever dares to read.\",\"translation\":\"La literatura demostr\\u00f3 ser intemporal, respirando a trav\\u00e9s de quien se atreve a leer.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-20 13:37:07\"},{\"content\":\"La biblioteca olvidada\",\"translation\":\"La biblioteca olvidada\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-12-17 14:07:56\"},{\"content\":\"Shakespearean heroes greeted her, Dickens\\u00e2\\u20ac\\u2122 ghosts sang of forgotten streets.\",\"translation\":\"Los h\\u00c3\\u00a9roes de Shakespeare la saludaban, los fantasmas de Dickens cantaban a las calles olvidadas.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-12-17 14:09:13\"},{\"content\":\"Clara realized she wasn\\u00e2\\u20ac\\u2122t just reading, she was inside.\",\"translation\":\"Clara se dio cuenta de que no s\\u00c3\\u00b3lo estaba leyendo, sino que estaba dentro.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-12-17 14:10:24\"},{\"content\":\"Night after night, she returned, restoring the library\\u00e2\\u20ac\\u2122s fading strength.\",\"translation\":\"Noche tras noche, regresaba, devolviendo a la biblioteca su fuerza menguante.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-12-17 14:10:38\"},{\"content\":\"But Clara knew she wasn\\u00e2\\u20ac\\u2122t saving books; they saved her.\",\"translation\":\"Pero Clara sab\\u00c3a que no estaba salvando libros; ellos la salvaban a ella.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-12-17 14:10:49\"}]', 1, 21, '2025-08-20 15:29:46'),
(167, 22, 'The Journey of Words', 'El viaje de las palabras', 'The Journey of Words\r\nEthan loved books more than anything in the world.\r\nHis suitcase was never clothes, but always full of novels.\r\nHe believed every journey began with reading, not with maps.\r\n\r\nOne summer, he boarded a train across distant green valleys.\r\nThe rhythm of wheels echoed like verses on old paper.\r\nHe opened Homer, and seas rose beyond the train window.\r\n\r\nMountains became Troyâ€™s walls, and fellow travelers looked like warriors.\r\nEach station felt like a new chapter waiting to unfold.\r\nThe world outside and inside his book merged into one.\r\n\r\nIn Italy, he carried Dante beneath Florenceâ€™s burning sunsets.\r\nEvery bridge whispered lines about exile, love, and redemption.\r\nHe recited softly, and the river replied with echoes.\r\n\r\nIn Spain, Don Quixote rode alongside buses and wandering tourists.\r\nWindmills near La Mancha turned like giants in slow dance.\r\nEthan laughed, certain literature had painted reality with bold colors.\r\n\r\nWeeks passed, and his journey stitched stories into living memory.\r\nNo city existed without a book to explain it.\r\nNo word lived unless a traveler carried it further.\r\n\r\nWhen he returned home, people asked what countries he visited.\r\nHe smiled: â€œI traveled through books, and books traveled through me.â€\r\nFor Ethan, every journey was literature, and literature was travel.', '[{\"content\":\"Ethan loved books more than anything in the world.\",\"translation\":\"Ethan amaba los libros m\\u00e1s que a nada en el mundo.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-25 04:34:30\"},{\"content\":\"Ethan loved books more than anything in the world.\",\"translation\":\"Ethan amaba los libros m\\u00e1s que a nada en el mundo.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-25 04:34:30\"},{\"content\":\"His suitcase was never clothes, but always full of novels.\",\"translation\":\"En su maleta nunca hab\\u00eda ropa, pero siempre estaba llena de novelas.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-25 04:34:56\"},{\"content\":\"He believed every journey began with reading, not with maps.\",\"translation\":\"Cre\\u00eda que todo viaje empezaba con la lectura, no con los mapas.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-25 04:35:21\"},{\"content\":\"One summer, he boarded a train across distant green valleys.\",\"translation\":\"Un verano, subi\\u00f3 a un tren que cruzaba valles verdes lejanos.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-25 04:35:42\"},{\"content\":\"The rhythm of wheels echoed like verses on old paper.\",\"translation\":\"El ritmo de las ruedas resonaba como versos en papel viejo.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-25 04:36:05\"},{\"content\":\"He opened Homer, and seas rose beyond the train window.\",\"translation\":\"Abri\\u00f3 Homer, y el mar se elev\\u00f3 m\\u00e1s all\\u00e1 de la ventanilla del tren.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-25 04:36:33\"},{\"content\":\"Mountains became Troy\\u2019s walls, and fellow travelers looked like warriors.\",\"translation\":\"Las monta\\u00f1as se convirtieron en murallas de Troya, y los compa\\u00f1eros de viaje parec\\u00edan guerreros.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-25 04:36:43\"},{\"content\":\"Each station felt like a new chapter waiting to unfold.\",\"translation\":\"Cada estaci\\u00f3n parec\\u00eda un nuevo cap\\u00edtulo a punto de abrirse.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-25 04:37:10\"},{\"content\":\"The world outside and inside his book merged into one.\",\"translation\":\"El mundo exterior y el interior de su libro se fundieron en uno solo.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-25 04:37:58\"},{\"content\":\"In Italy, he carried Dante beneath Florence\\u2019s burning sunsets.\",\"translation\":\"En Italia, llev\\u00f3 a Dante bajo los ardientes atardeceres de Florencia.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-25 04:38:41\"},{\"content\":\"Every bridge whispered lines about exile, love, and redemption.\",\"translation\":\"Cada puente susurraba l\\u00edneas sobre el exilio, el amor y la redenci\\u00f3n.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-25 04:38:53\"},{\"content\":\"He