h me.\\u201d\",\"translation\":\"Sonri\\u00f3: \\\"Viaj\\u00e9 a trav\\u00e9s de los libros, y los libros viajaron a trav\\u00e9s de m\\u00ed\\\".\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-25 04:42:18\"},{\"content\":\"For Ethan, every journey was literature, and literature was travel.\",\"translation\":\"Para Ethan, todo viaje era literatura, y la literatura era viajar.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-25 04:42:46\"},{\"content\":\"Ethan loved books more than anything in the world.\",\"translation\":\"Ethan amaba los libros m\\u00e1s que a nada en el mundo.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-25 15:31:49\"},{\"content\":\"Ethan loved books more than anything in the world.\",\"translation\":\"Ethan amaba los libros m\\u00e1s que a nada en el mundo.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-26 05:45:46\"},{\"content\":\"The Journey of Words\",\"translation\":\"El viaje de las palabras\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-12-21 21:25:41\"}]', 1, 21, '2025-08-20 15:43:39'),
(168, 22, 'The House of Echoes', 'La casa de los ecos', 'The House of Echoes\r\nSophia returned to her grandmotherâ€™s house after many years.\r\nThe wooden floor creaked, repeating childhood steps she once made.\r\nFamily photographs lined the walls, faces smiling from faded frames.\r\n\r\nHer grandfatherâ€™s chair still waited, though he passed long ago.\r\nShe touched its armrest, remembering stories he told at night.\r\nHis voice seemed alive, whispering through the silent living room.\r\n\r\nIn the kitchen, the scent of cinnamon lingered faintly.\r\nHer mother once baked pies, filling Sundays with warmth.\r\nThe memory wrapped her heart, both sweet and heavy.\r\n\r\nUpstairs, she found her brotherâ€™s drawings under an old desk.\r\nDragons, castles, and heroes sketched with innocent imagination.\r\nThough he lived abroad now, the house kept his presence.\r\n\r\nSophia realized each corner preserved echoes of family moments.\r\nThe house itself was a guardian of loveâ€™s history.\r\nWalls held laughter, arguments, reconciliations, and quiet celebrations.\r\n\r\nShe sat by the window, watching dusk paint the yard.\r\nSuddenly, she felt less alone, surrounded by invisible company.\r\nFamily, she thought, is not gone when the heart remembers.\r\n\r\nWhen she left, she locked the door with care.\r\nNot to abandon, but to honor what stayed inside.\r\nFor family lived beyond time, echoing in every heartbeat.', '[{\"content\":\"Sophia returned to her grandmother\\u2019s house after many years.\",\"translation\":\"Sof\\u00eda volvi\\u00f3 a casa de su abuela despu\\u00e9s de muchos a\\u00f1os.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-20 13:47:22\"},{\"content\":\"Sophia returned to her grandmother\\u2019s house after many years.\",\"translation\":\"Sof\\u00eda volvi\\u00f3 a casa de su abuela despu\\u00e9s de muchos a\\u00f1os.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-20 13:47:22\"},{\"content\":\"The wooden floor creaked, repeating childhood steps she once made.\",\"translation\":\"El suelo de made