(171, 22, 'Adjectives are words', 'Los adjetivos son palabras', 'Adjectives are words that describe or modify nouns, giving more information about them.\r\nIn English, adjectives usually come before the noun, like in \"a beautiful house\" example.\r\nAdjectives can describe color, size, shape, age, origin, material, or even opinion.\r\nFor example: \"She wore a red dress\", where \"red\" is an adjective describing color.\r\nSize adjectives include words like \"big, small, tall, short, huge, tiny\" for different situations.\r\nShape adjectives describe form, such as \"round, square, triangular, flat, oval, rectangular, spiral\".\r\nAge adjectives tell us how old something is: \"new, old, young, ancient, modern\".\r\nOrigin adjectives show where something or someone comes from, like \"Italian, American, French, Asian\".\r\nMaterial adjectives describe the substance of an object, like \"wooden table, plastic bottle, golden ring\".\r\nOpinion adjectives express feelings about something, for example: \"The movie was interesting and exciting\".\r\nMany adjectives can be graded using comparative and superlative forms, like \"taller, tallest, more beautiful\".\r\nFor example: \"My house is bigger than yours, but his house is the biggest\".\r\nSome adjectives are irregular, like \"good, better, best\" or \"bad, worse, worst\".\r\nWe also use adjectives after the verb \"to be\", as in \"She is happy\".\r\nAdjectives can combine with adverbs for emphasis, like \"extremely important, very useful, incredibly difficult\".\r\nIn English, adjectives never change form for gender or number, unlike some other languages.\r\nWe use multiple adjectives in a specific order: opinion, size, age, shape, color, origin, material.\r\nFor example: \"She bought a beautiful small old round red Italian wooden jewelry box\".\r\nAdjectives are essential for communication because they enrich descriptions and make language more precise.', '[{\"content\":\"Adjectives are words that describe or modify nouns, giving more information about them.\",\"translation\":\"Los adjetivos son palabras que describen o modifican a los sustantivos, aportando m\\u00e1s informaci\\u00f3n sobre ellos.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-28 12:03:02\"},{\"content\":\"In English, adjectives usually come before the noun, like in \\\"a beautiful house\\\" example.\",\"translation\":\"En ingl\\u00e9s, los adjetivos suelen ir delante del sustantivo, como en el ejemplo de \\\"a beautiful house\\\".\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-28 12:03:22\"},{\"content\":\"Adjectives can describe color, size, shape, age, origin, material, or even opinion.\",\"translation\":\"Los adjetivos pueden describir el color, el tama\\u00f1o, la forma, la edad, el origen, el material o incluso la opini\\u00f3n.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-28 12:03:59\"},{\"content\":\"For example: \\\"She wore a red dress\\\", where \\\"red\\\" is an adjective describing color.\",\"translation\":\"Por ejemplo: \\\"Llevaba un vestido rojo\\\", donde \\\"rojo\\\" es un adjetivo que describe el color.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-28 12:04:43\"},{\"content\":\"Size adjectives include words like \\\"big, small, tall, short, huge, tiny\\\" for different situations.\",\"translation\":\"Los adjetivos de tama\\u00f1o incluyen palabras como \\\"grande, peque\\u00f1o, alto, bajo, enorme, diminuto\\\" para diferentes situaciones.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-28 12:05:20\"},{\"content\":\"Shape adjectives describe form, such as \\\"round, square, triangular, flat, oval, rectangular, spiral\\\".\",\"translation\":\"Los adjetivos de forma describen la forma, como \\\"redonda, cuadrada, triangular, plana, ovalada, rectangular, en espiral\\\".\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-28 12:05:46\"},{\"content\":\"Age adjectives tell us how old something is: \\\"new, old, young, ancient, modern\\\".\",\"translation\":\"Los adjetivos de edad nos indican la antig\\u00fcedad de algo: \\\"nuevo, viejo, joven, antiguo, moderno\\\".\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-28 12:06:28\"},{\"content\":\"Origin adjectives show where something or someone comes from, like \\\"Italian, American, French, Asian\\\".\",\"translation\":\"Los adjetivos de origen muestran de d\\u00f3nde procede algo o alguien, como \\\"italiano, americano, franc\\u00e9s, asi\\u00e1tico\\\".\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-28 12:06:49\"},{\"content\":\"Material adjectives describe the substance of an object, like \\\"wooden table, plastic bottle, golden ring\\\".\",\"translation\":\"Los adjetivos materiales describen la sustancia de un objeto, como \\\"mesa de madera, botella de pl\\u00e1stico, anillo de oro\\\".\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-28 12:07:38\"},{\"content\":\"Material adjectives describe the substance of an object, like \\\"wooden table, plastic bottle, golden ring\\\".\",\"translation\":\"Los adjetivos materiales describen la sustancia de un objeto, como \\\"mesa de madera, botella de pl\\u00e1stico, anillo de oro\\\".\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-28 12:07:38\"},{\"content\":\"Opinion adjectives express feelings about something, for example: \\\"The movie was interesting and exciting\\\".\",\"translation\":\"Los adjetivos de opini\\u00f3n expresan sentimientos sobre algo, por ejemplo: \\\"La pel\\u00edcula fue interesante y emocionante\\\".\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-28 12:08:02\"},{\"content\":\"Many adjectives can be graded using comparative and superlative forms, like \\\"taller, tallest, more beautiful\\\".\",\"translation\":\"Muchos adjetivos pueden calificarse utilizando formas comparativas y superlativas, como \\\"m\\u00e1s alto, m\\u00e1s alto, m\\u00e1s bello\\\".\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-28 12:08:25\"},{\"content\":\"For example: \\\"My house is bigger than yours, but his house is the biggest\\\".\",\"translation\":\"Por ejemplo: \\\"Mi casa es m\\u00e1s grande que la tuya, pero la suya es la m\\u00e1s grande\\\".\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-28 12:08:49\"},{\"content\":\"Some adjectives are irregular, like \\\"good, better, best\\\" or \\\"bad, worse, worst\\\".\",\"translation\":\"Algun