(173, 12, 'JavaScript Vocabulary', NULL, 'JavaScript is a programming language used to create dynamic web pages, interactive applications, and many useful tools online.\r\n\r\nAn important part of JavaScript is working with arrays, which are lists of values stored in a single variable.\r\n\r\nThe method push () adds a new element at the end of an array, making the collection grow larger.\r\n\r\nThe method pop () removes the last element of an array, which is helpful when cleaning or updating data.\r\n\r\nThe method shift () removes the first element of an array and shifts the remaining items one position left.\r\n\r\nThe method unshift () adds one or more elements to the beginning of an array, making it easy to update a list.\r\n\r\nThe method map () creates a new array by applying a function to each element of the original array.\r\n\r\nThe method filter () returns a new array with only the elements that pass a certain condition or test.\r\n\r\nThe method reduce () executes a function on each element of the array, producing a single accumulated result value.\r\n\r\nObjects in JavaScript represent collections of key and value pairs, used to describe structured data.\r\n\r\nThe method Object.keys () returns an array of all the property names of an object, useful for iteration.\r\n\r\nThe method Object.values () returns an array of all the values inside the object, ignoring the keys.\r\n\r\nThe method Object.entries () returns an array of arrays, each containing a key and its corresponding value.\r\n\r\nFunctions in JavaScript are blocks of code designed to perform a particular task when called or executed.\r\n\r\nAn arrow function is a shorter way to write a function, often used for cleaner and more modern code.\r\n\r\nLoops are structures that repeat a block of code while a condition is true, or for a fixed number of times.\r\n\r\nThe for loop repeats code a specific number of times, using an index that increases each iteration.\r\n\r\nThe while loop continues running as long as the given condition is true, often used for unknown repetitions.\r\n\r\nThe forEach () method is another way to loop through arrays, applying a function to each element in sequence.\r\n\r\nJavaScript vocabulary grows with practice, and learning these methods makes programming faster, cleaner, and much more effective.\r\n\r\n¿Quieres que lo prepare también con ejemplos cortos de código en inglés, o prefieres solo explicaciones en texto para tu app?', '[{\"content\":\"JavaScript is a programming language used to create dynamic web pages, interactive applications, and many useful tools online.\",\"translation\":\"JavaScript es un lenguaje de programaci\\u00f3n utilizado para crear p\\u00e1ginas web din\\u00e1micas, aplicaciones interactivas y muchas herramientas \\u00fatiles en l\\u00ednea.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-05 14:17:07\"},{\"content\":\"An important part of JavaScript is working with arrays, which are lists of values stored in a single variable.\",\"translation\":\"Una parte importante de JavaScript es trabajar con arrays, que son listas de valores almacenados en una \\u00fanica variable.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-05 14:17:31\"},{\"content\":\"The method push () adds a new element at the end of an array, making the collection grow larger.\",\"translation\":\"El m\\u00e9todo push () a\\u00f1ade un nuevo elemento al final de un array, haciendo que la colecci\\u00f3n aumente de tama\\u00f1o.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-05 14:17:50\"},{\"content\":\"The method pop () removes the last element of an array, which is helpful when cleaning or updating data.\",\"translation\":\"El m\\u00e9todo pop () elimina el \\u00faltimo elemento de un array, lo que resulta \\u00fatil a la hora de limpiar o actualizar datos.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-05 14:18:13\"},{\"content\":\"The method shift () removes the first element of an array and shifts the remaining items one position left.\",\"translation\":\"El m\\u00e9todo shift () elimina el primer elemento de una matriz y desplaza el resto de elementos una posici\\u00f3n hacia la izquierda.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-05 14:18:31\"},{\"content\":\"The method unshift () adds one or more elements to the beginning of an array, making it easy to update a list.\",\"translation\":\"El m\\u00e9todo unshift () a\\u00f1ade uno o m\\u00e1s elementos al principio de un array, facilitando la actualizaci\\u00f3n de una lista.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-05 14:18:49\"},{\"content\":\"The method map () creates a new array by applying a function to each element of the original array.\",\"translation\":\"El m\\u00e9todo map () crea un nuevo array aplicando una funci\\u00f3n a cada elemento del array original.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-05 14:19:00\"},{\"content\":\"The method filter () returns a new array with only the elements that pass a certain condition or test.\",\"translation\":\"El m\\u00e9todo filter () devuelve un nuevo array con s\\u00f3lo los elementos que pasan una determinada condici\\u00f3n o test.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-05 14:19:02\"},{\"content\":\"The method reduce () executes a function on each element of the array, producing a single accumulated result value.\",\"translation\":\"El m\\u00e9todo reduce () ejecuta una funci\\u00f3n en cada elemento de la matriz, produciendo un \\u00fanico valor de resultado acumulado.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-05 14:19:06\"},{\"content\":\"Objects in JavaScript represent collections of key and value pairs, used to describe structured data.\",\"translation\":\"En JavaScript, los objetos representan colecciones de pares de claves y valores que se utilizan para describir datos estructurados.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-05 14:19:09\"},{\"content\":\"The method Object.keys () returns an array of all the property names of an object, useful for iteration.\",\"translation\":\"El m\\u00e9todo Object.keys () devuelve una matriz con todos los nombres de las propiedades de un objeto, \\u00fatil para la iteraci\\u00f3n.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-05 14:19:27\"},{\"co