(174, 12, 'Git is a powerful', NULL, 'Git is a powerful version control system that helps developers track changes in their code over time.\r\nWith Git, you can create snapshots of your project, allowing you to move back when something goes wrong.\r\nThe most basic command in Git is git init, which initializes a new repository inside your project folder.\r\nAfter initialization, you can use git add followed by filenames to stage specific changes for the next commit.\r\nOnce changes are staged, the git commit command records a snapshot with a descriptive message for future reference.\r\nIf you want to see your project history, you can type git log to list previous commits and messages.\r\nWhen mistakes happen, git status and git restore help you check current modifications and reset unwanted changes quickly.\r\nBranches in Git allow developers to experiment with features separately without affecting the main working version.\r\nTo create a new branch, use git branch followed by a name, then switch with git checkout.\r\nMerging branches brings together different development lines, which is done using git merge inside your chosen branch.\r\nSometimes conflicts appear when two branches modify the same lines, and you must resolve them manually before merging.\r\nGitHub is an online platform that hosts Git repositories and makes collaboration easier for teams across the world.\r\nYou can push local commits to GitHub using git push, which uploads your branch to the remote repository.\r\nTo download updates from GitHub, the git pull command fetches changes and merges them into your current branch.\r\nIf you only want to see updates without merging, the git fetch command retrieves changes for later review.\r\nCollaboration on GitHub is managed with pull requests, which let others review and discuss code before merging changes.\r\nYou can clone a repository from GitHub with git clone, which creates a full local copy for development work.\r\nSSH keys or HTTPS authentication are used to securely connect your computer with GitHub for pushing and pulling.\r\nGood practice recommends committing often, writing clear messages, and pushing regularly to keep your project synchronized.\r\nBy combining Git locally and GitHub remotely, developers achieve efficient workflows, teamwork, and reliable project version management.', '[{\"content\":\"Git is a powerful version control system that helps developers track changes in their code over time.\",\"translation\":\"Git es un potente sistema de control de versiones que ayuda a los desarrolladores a realizar un seguimiento de los cambios en su c\\u00f3digo a lo largo del tiempo.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-16 10:20:12\"},{\"content\":\"With Git, you can create snapshots of your project, allowing you to move back when something goes wrong.\",\"translation\":\"Con Git, puedes crear instant\\u00e1neas de tu proyecto, lo que te permite retroceder cuando algo va mal.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-16 10:20:33\"},{\"content\":\"The most basic command in Git is git init, which initializes a new repository inside your project folder.\",\"translation\":\"El comando m\\u00e1s b\\u00e1sico en Git es git init, que inicializa un nuevo repositorio dentro de la carpeta de tu proyecto.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-16 10:20:51\"},{\"content\":\"After initialization, you can use git add followed by filenames to stage specific changes for the next commit.\",\"translation\":\"Tras la inicializaci\\u00f3n, puedes usar git add seguido de los nombres de los archivos para preparar cambios espec\\u00edficos para la siguiente confirmaci\\u00f3n.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-16 10:21:11\"},{\"content\":\"Once changes are staged, the git commit command records a snapshot with a descriptive message for future reference.\",\"translation\":\"Una vez que los cambios se ponen en escena, el comando git commit registra una instant\\u00e1nea con un mensaje descriptivo para futuras referencias.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-16 10:21:36\"},{\"content\":\"If you want to see your project history, you can type git log to list previous commits and messages.\",\"translation\":\"Si quieres ver el historial de tu proyecto, puedes escribir git log para listar los commits y mensajes anteriores.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-16 10:22:01\"},{\"content\":\"When mistakes happen, git status and git restore help you check current modifications and reset unwanted changes quickly.\",\"translation\":\"Cuando se producen errores, git status y git restore te ayudan a comprobar las modificaciones actuales y a restablecer r\\u00e1pidamente los cambios no deseados.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-16 10:22:18\"},{\"content\":\"Branches in Git allow developers to experiment with features separately without affecting the main working version.\",\"translation\":\"Las ramas en Git permiten a los desarrolladores experimentar con caracter\\u00edsticas por separado sin afectar a la versi\\u00f3n principal de trabajo.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-16 10:22:41\"},{\"content\":\"To create a new branch, use git branch followed by a name, then switch with git checkout.\",\"translation\":\"Para crear una nueva rama, utilice git branch seguido de un nombre, y luego cambie con git checkout.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-16 10:23:02\"},{\"content\":\"Merging branches brings together different development lines, which is done using git merge inside your chosen branch.\",\"translation\":\"La fusi\\u00f3n de ramas re\\u00fane diferentes l\\u00edneas de desarrollo, lo que se hace utilizando git merge dentro de la rama elegida.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-16 10:23:22\"},{\"content\":\"Sometimes conflicts appear when two branches modify the same lines, and you must resolve them manually before merging.\",\"translation\":\"A veces aparecen conflictos cuando dos ramas modifican las mismas l\\u00edneas, y hay que resolverlos manualmente antes de fusionarlas.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-16 10:23:44\"},{\"content\":\"GitHub is an online platform that hosts Git repositories and makes collaboration easier for teams across the world.\",\"translation\":\"GitHub es una plataforma en l\\u00ednea que aloja repositorios Git y facilita la colaboraci\\u00f3n entre equipos de todo el mundo.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-16 10:24:05\"},{\"content\":\"You can push local commits to GitHub using git push, which uploads your branch to the remote repository.\",\"translation\":\"Puedes enviar commits locales a GitHub usando git push, que sube tu rama al repositorio remoto.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-16 10:24:35\"},{\"content\":\"To download updates from GitHub, the git pull command fetches changes and merges them into your current branch.\",\"translation\":\"Para descargar actualizaciones de GitHub, el comando git pull recupera los cambios y los fusiona en tu rama actual.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-16 10:24:54\"},{\"content\":\"If you only want to see updates without merging, the git fetch command retrieves changes for later review.\",\"translation\":\"Si s\\u00f3lo quieres ver las actualizaciones sin fusionar, el comando git fetch recupera los cambios para su posterior revisi\\u00f3n.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-16 10:25:15\"},{\"content\":\"Collaboration on GitHub is managed with pull requests, which let others review and discuss code before merging changes.\",\"translation\":\"La colaboraci\\u00f3n en GitHub se gestiona con pull requests, que permiten a otros revisar y discutir el c\\u00f3digo antes de fusionar los cambios.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-16 10:25:33\"},{\"content\":\"You can clone a repository from GitHub with git clone, which creates a full local copy for development work.\",\"translation\":\"Puedes clonar un repositorio desde GitHub con git clone, que crea una copia local completa para el trabajo de desarrollo.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-16 10:25:55\"},{\"content\":\"SSH keys or HTTPS authentication are used to securely connect your computer with GitHub for pushing and pulling.\",\"translation\":\"Las claves SSH o la autenticaci\\u00f3n HTTPS se utilizan para conectar de forma segura tu ordenador con GitHub para hacer push y pull.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-16 10:26:14\"},{\"content\":\"Good practice recommends committing often, writing clear messages, and pushing regularly to keep your project synchronized.\",\"translation\":\"Las buenas pr\\u00e1cticas recomiendan comprometerse a menudo, redactar mensajes claros y empujar con regularidad para mantener el proyecto sincronizado.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-16 10:26:37\"},{\"content\":\"By combining Git locally and GitHub remotely, developers achieve efficient workflows, teamwork, and reliable project version management.\",\"translation\":\"Combinando Git localmente y GitHub remotamente, los desarrolladores consiguen flujos de trabajo eficientes, trabajo en equipo y una gesti\\u00f3n fiable de las versiones de los proyectos.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-16 10:27:00\"},{\"content\":\"Git is a powerful version control system that helps developers track changes in their code over time.\",\"translation\":\"Git es un potente sistema de control de versiones que ayuda a los desarrolladores a realizar un seguimiento de los cambios en su c\\u00f3digo a lo largo del tiempo.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-17 13:54:11\"},{\"content\":\"With Git, you can create snapshots of your project, allowing you to move back when something goes wrong.\",\"translation\":\"Con Git, puedes crear instant\\u00e1neas de tu proyecto, lo que te permite retroceder cuando algo va mal.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-17 13:54:32\"},{\"content\":\"The most basic command in Git is git init, which initializes a new repository inside your project folder.\",\"translation\":\"El comando m\\u00e1s b\\u00e1sico en Git es git init, que inicializa un nuevo repositorio dentro de la carpeta de tu proyecto.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-17 13:54:51\"},{\"content\":\"After initialization, you can use git add followed by filenames to stage specific changes for the next commit.\",\"translation\":\"Tras la inicializaci\\u00f3n, puedes usar git add seguido de los nombres de los archivos para preparar cambios espec\\u00edficos para la siguiente confirmaci\\u00f3n.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-17 13:55:12\"},{\"content\":\"Once changes are staged, the git commit command records a snapshot with a descriptive message for future reference.\",\"translation\":\"Una vez que los cambios se ponen en escena, el comando git commit registra una instant\\u00e1nea con un mensaje descriptivo para futuras referencias.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-17 13:55:33\"},{\"content\":\"If you want to see your project history, you can type git log to list previous commits and messages.\",\"translation\":\"Si quieres ver el historial de tu proyecto, puedes escribir git log para listar los commits y mensajes anteriores.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-17 13:55:55\"},{\"content\":\"When mistakes happen, git status and git restore help you check current modifications and reset unwanted changes quickly.\",\"translation\":\"Cuando se producen errores, git status y git restore te ayudan a comprobar las modificaciones actuales y a restablecer r\\u00e1pidamente los cambios no deseados.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-17 13:56:12\"},{\"content\":\"Branches in Git allow developers to experiment with features separately without affecting the main working version.\",\"translation\":\"Las ramas en Git permiten a los desarrolladores experimentar con caracter\\u00edsticas por separado sin afectar a la versi\\u00f3n principal de trabajo.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-17 13:56:35\"},{\"content\":\"To create a new branch, use git branch followed by a name, then switch with git checkout.\",\"translation\":\"Para crear una nueva rama, utilice git branch seguido de un nombre, y luego cambie con git checkout.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-17 13:56:56\"},{\"content\":\"Merging branches brings together different development lines, which is done using git merge inside your chosen branch.\",\"translation\":\"La fusi\\u00f3n de ramas re\\u00fane diferentes l\\u00edneas de desarrollo, l